### ContactShadows: Render Soft Shadows

Source: https://context7.com/pmndrs/drei/llms.txt

Renders soft contact shadows beneath objects in a react-three-fiber scene. It offers configurable resolution, blur, and opacity for balancing performance and visual quality. The component can be used for basic shadow rendering or for high-quality static shadows that render only once.

```jsx
import { Canvas } from '@react-three/fiber'
import { ContactShadows, OrbitControls } from '@react-three/drei'

function App() {
  return (
    <Canvas>
      {/* Basic contact shadow */}
      <ContactShadows
        position={[0, -0.5, 0]}
        opacity={0.5}
        scale={10}
        blur={1}
        far={10}
        resolution={256}
        color="#000000"
      />

      {/* High quality static shadow (renders once) */}
      <ContactShadows
        frames={1}
        position={[0, -0.5, 0]}
        opacity={0.75}
        scale={20}
        blur={2.5}
        far={4}
        resolution={512}
      />

      <mesh position={[0, 0.5, 0]}>
        <boxGeometry />
        <meshStandardMaterial color="orange" />
      </mesh>

      {/* Ground plane for reference */}
      <mesh rotation={[-Math.PI / 2, 0, 0]} position={[0, -0.5, 0]}>
        <planeGeometry args={[20, 20]} />
        <meshStandardMaterial color="#f0f0f0" />
      </mesh>

      <OrbitControls />
      <ambientLight intensity={0.5} />
      <directionalLight position={[5, 5, 5]} />
    </Canvas>
  )
}
```

### AccumulativeShadows

Source: https://github.com/pmndrs/drei/blob/master/docs/staging/accumulative-shadows.mdx

A planar, Y-up oriented shadow-catcher that can accumulate into soft shadows and has zero performance impact after all frames have accumulated. It can be temporal, it will accumulate over time, or instantaneous, which might be expensive depending on how many frames you render.

You must pair it with lightsources (and scene objects!) that cast shadows, which go into the children slot. Best use it with the `RandomizedLight` component, which jiggles a set of lights around, creating realistic raycast-like shadows and ambient occlusion.

--------------------------------

### RandomizedLight

Source: https://github.com/pmndrs/drei/blob/master/docs/staging/randomized-light.mdx

A randomized light that internally runs multiple lights and jiggles them. You would normally pair it with `AccumulativeShadows`. This component is context aware; when paired with AccumulativeShadows, it will take the number of frames from its parent.

--------------------------------

### SoftShadows

Source: https://github.com/pmndrs/drei/blob/master/docs/shaders/soft-shadows.mdx

Injects percent closer soft shadows (pcss) into threes shader chunk. Mounting and unmounting this component will lead to all shaders being be re-compiled, although it will only cause overhead if SoftShadows is mounted after the scene has already rendered, if it mounts with everything else in your scene shaders will compile naturally.
